                "name": "grafana",
                "namespace": "auth-service",
                "notes": "1. Get your 'admin' user password by running:\n\n   kubectl get secret --namespace auth-service grafana -o jsonpath=\"{.data.admin-password}\" | base64 --decode ; echo\n\n\n2. The Grafana server can be accessed via port 80 on the following DNS name from within your cluster:\n\n   grafana.auth-service.svc.cluster.local\n\n   Get the Grafana URL to visit by running these commands in the same shell:\n     export NODE_PORT=$(kubectl get --namespace auth-service -o jsonpath=\"{.spec.ports[0].nodePort}\" services grafana)\n     export NODE_IP=$(kubectl get nodes --namespace auth-service -o jsonpath=\"{.items[0].status.addresses[0].address}\")\n     echo http://$NODE_IP:$NODE_PORT\n\n3. Login with the password from step 1 and the username: admin\n#################################################################################\n######   WARNING: Persistence is disabled!!! You will lose your data when   #####\n######            the Grafana pod is terminated.                            #####\n#################################################################################\n",
                "revision": 1,
                "values": "{\"adminPassword\":\"admin\",\"service\":{\"nodePort\":30030,\"type\":\"NodePort\"}}",
                "version": "10.5.15"
